<content type="str">By Chioma Obinna 
 
To some people, snoring means little or nothing. But some people can kill when you snore around them. For instance, a 30- year – old commercial motorcyclist allegedly beat his wife to stupor for snoring recently. 
 
However, while snoring can result in conflict among family members and constitute a nuisance to frustrated bed partners, it is no longer something to ignore. This is because experts say people who snore risk heart diseases.  They are also of the view that snoring is sometimes a warning sign  that needs a doctor’s evaluation on sleeping disorders such as obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) or sleep-related breathing problems. Studies have shown that one in every four people snore. 
 
